	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1R"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Nashville</placeName> <date>May 8<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1853</date></p>
				<p><persName>Mr Editor</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Reverend Sir&#44;&#8212;</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Being a constant<lb/> reader of your truly valuable periodical&#44;<lb/> I have perceived that you take a<lb/> lively interest in recording the procee<lb/>dings of Jewish affairs throughout<lb/> the world  Hence I take the liberty<lb/> of presenting to you a brief notice<lb/> of the progress of Judaism in<lb/> the city of <placeName>Nashville</placeName>  There are resi&#45;<lb/>ding here about thirty Israelites&#44; who<lb/> have for the last two years in exis<lb/>tance an association for Jewish benef<lb/>icial purposes called &#40;Margen<lb/> <persName>David</persName>&#41; Shield of <persName>David</persName>  This society<lb/> has during the short time of its<lb/> existence acquired <del>f</del> a &#40;Bais Hackfor<lb/>us&#44;&#41; Burial Ground and it is in<lb/> contemplation to from it into a<lb/> Congregation&#44; for this purpose&#44; they<lb/> have for some time <add>past</add> a temporary<lb/> synagogue at the house of <persName>Isaac<lb/> Garretson Esqr.</persName> through the kindness of</p>
			<pb n="1V"/>
				<p>that gentleman.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Revd Mr Iser</persName> has been<lb/> appointed&#44; Hasen&#44; Schohul and<lb/> Instructor of the Hebrew <sic>Sanguage</sic>&#44;<lb/> during the past Holy days&#8212;<lb/> Divine Services were performed in<lb/> a very <sic>approbiate</sic> manner<lb/> and on the <date>second Passover day</date><lb/> a very interesting discourse was<lb/> delivered by <persName>Revd Mr Iser</persName> a gentleman<lb/> of high<del>ly</del> Jewish qualifications.</p>
			<p rend="indent(9)">The Society<lb/> is also using every exertion to erect<lb/> speedily a permanent Synagogue<lb/> and using means for its incorpor<lb/>ation at the next Legislature.<lb/>  At an <sic>anual</sic> election held last<lb/> <date>Sunday</date> the following named<lb/> gentleman were elected as officers<lb/> for one year</p>
				<list type="simple">
				<head></head>
				<item><persName>H. Harris Esqr</persName> President</item>
				<item><persName>E. Wolf Esqr</persName> Vice President</item>
				<item><persName>Messrs E. Franklin</persName>&#44; <persName>L. Lande</persName> and<lb/> <persName>Louis Sohn</persName> Trustees</item>
				<item><persName>Mr L. Hillman</persName>&#44; Secretary</item>
				<item><persName>Mr Marx Elsback</persName>&#44; Treasurer</item>
				</list>
				<p>Hoping that I have not trespassed</p>
			<pb n="2R"/>
				<p>too much on your time and space</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">I remain with high regards</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Your <sic>Obediant</sic> Servant</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)"><persName role="author">Lem<add>&#63;</add> Hillman</persName></p>
				<p>N.B. Have the kindness to insert those<lb/> Hebrew expressions which I <sic>has</sic> written<lb/> in English in the Hebrew Language.</p>
		</body>
